The paper focuses on studying the potential for adversarial manipulation in a multi-agent system, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses security against impersonation attacks, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of graphical coordination games and decision-making rules suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact on Nash equilibria, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT).
